text: Love this coffee shop. It has affordable and delicious food. Won’t be bored cuz there’s amazing cai fan, one of my favourite KKM and a pretty decent mala stall! Possibly the best coffeeshop in Bukit Panjang area. You won’t get hot and sweaty because it is really well ventilated. Kudos to the team for keeping it clean and comfy as well!
Only coffeeshop in the neighbourhood.  Food choices are decent. Koka noodles is unique.

A very nice coffeeshop. Just sad it is so hidden. I've passed this area so many times & today was the first time I heard about it from someone so I went to find it. It is very peaceful because you are not aware of all the traffic, just a block away. The staff were all very friendly. Best of all was that the food on the plate I received looked just as good as the one in the picture and I also really enjoyed it.

One of the male cleaning staff who works during weekend nights is very rude and unfriendly. My friends and I were standing around a dirty table waiting for it to be cleaned when the cleaner approached us from behind to clean it, we were unaware that we were blocking him and instead of politely asking us to give way, he stared and glared at us instead in an aggressive manner which really ruined the overall mood of our experience. Would complain to the management but I cant find their contact info. Food is very sub-par.

This coffee shop is open 24 hours. Do note that only dim sum and the coffee stall are open 24 hours. During breakfast, there's a famous Koka Mee stall and also a stall that serves economic bee hoon and nasi lemak. In the afternoons and evenings there is Economic Rice, Bak Kut Teh, Chicken Rice, Char Kway Teow, Hokkien Mee, Carrot Cake, Oyster Omelette, Prawn Noodles, Fish Ball Mee, Hawker Western Food and Zi Char.
